<h2 id="problem">Problem</h2>

<p>This is the start of a series of blog posts where I try to build an online personal budgeting system.</p>

<p>The motivation for this was me trying to do a household budget usin</p>

<p>With <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_banking">Open Banking</a> approaching a common service to classify income and expenditure for bank statement transactions is not currently available on the market.</p>

<p>The ability for a consumer to categorise their transactions sits within varied personal finance providers (eg. pocketbook, mint).</p>

<h2 id="solution">Solution</h2>

<p>An API that uses <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Named-entity_recognition">Named Entity Recognition</a> to identifies a consumers bank statement into the below groups:</p>

<p>Why â€“&gt; classification (eg Holiday travel) &amp; sub-category (flights) Who â€“&gt; company originating the charge When â€“&gt; Date time &amp; location How â€“&gt; Method of transfer (EftPos, cash withdraw, direct debit, credit card) What â€“&gt; Type of transaction is it? Dishonour, Overdrawn, Interest, Fees, Credit, Debit</p>

<p>-â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”-</p>

<h2 id="key-metrics">Key Metrics</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Correct classifications</li>
  <li>API Usage</li>
  <li>Website signups</li>
  <li>Website classification requests</li>
  <li>Percent of statements marked as correct (accurately identified)</li>
  <li>Unique Value Proposition</li>
  <li>We offer an open solution to personal financial statement classification.</li>
</ul>

